ctd_show_skew_group(25.10)                          ctd_show_skew_group(25.10)

Name
       ctd_show_skew_group - Shows the specified skew group in the CTD window

Syntax
       ctd_show_skew_group

       [-help]

       [-id <window_id_name>]

       -skew_group <skew_group_name>

       Shows the specified skew group in the CTD window.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each ctd_show_skew_group  parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man  ctd_show_skew_group.

       -id <window_id_name>
              Specifies the CTD window ID. The default value is the ID of  the
              current active CTD window.

       -skew_group <skew_group_name>
              Specifies the name of the skew group. This is a required parame-
              ter.

Example
       Use  the  following command to show the specified skew group in the CTD
       window:

       ctd_show_skew_group -skew_group m_rcc_clk/PM_HL_FUNC

